HAP 602: Statistics in Health Services Management. 3 credits.
Focuses on descriptive and inferential statistics with applications of various statistical techniques to health services management. Topics include sampling, measures of central tendency and dispersion, probability distributions, hypothesis testing, analysis of variance, correlation, linear regression, and chi-square analysis. Offered by Health Administration & Policy. May not be repeated for credit.
