HAP 635: Role of Government in Health Care and Public Health. 3 credits.
Provides a foundation for how and why federal and state governments are involved in health care and public health. Introduces students to contemporary public policies that address inequities in access and quality of public health and health care services. The process of how public health policy is formulated, implemented and evaluated is covered in detail. Offered by Health Administration & Policy. May not be repeated for credit.
