HAP 761: Philosophy of Science and Research Methods. 3 credits.
Introduces the philosophy of science and methods used to conduct health services research. Examines the justification of knowledge claims (epistemology), approaches to research study design, and the application of analytic methods and data to develop knowledge in field of health services research. Offered by Health Administration & Policy. May not be repeated for credit.
